#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn51.20"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn51.20:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 51 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 51 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.20:0.2"
msgid "2. Pāsādakampanavagga "
msgstr "2. Shaking the Stilt Longhouse "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn51.20:0.3"
msgid "20. Vibhaṅgasutta "
msgstr "20. Analysis "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn51.20:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā honti mahānisaṃsā”. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, when the four bases of psychic power are developed and cultivated they’re very fruitful and beneficial. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.277, sc2
msgctxt "sn51.20:2.1"
msgid "Kathaṃ bhāvitā ca, bhikkhave, cattāro iddhipādā kathaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā honti mahānisaṃsā? "
msgstr "How so? "

msgctxt "sn51.20:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti—"
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm, and active effort. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:2.3"
msgid "iti me chando na ca atilīno bhavissati, na ca atippaggahito bhavissati, na ca ajjhattaṃ saṅkhitto bhavissati, na ca bahiddhā vikkhitto bhavissati. "
msgstr "They think: ‘My enthusiasm won’t be too lax or too tense. And it’ll be neither constricted internally nor scattered externally.’ "

msgctxt "sn51.20:2.4"
msgid "Pacchāpuresaññī ca viharati—"
msgstr "And they meditate perceiving continuity: "

msgctxt "sn51.20:2.5"
msgid "yathā pure tathā pacchā, yathā pacchā tathā pure; "
msgstr "as before, so after; as after, so before; "

msgctxt "sn51.20:2.6"
msgid "yathā adho tathā uddhaṃ, yathā uddhaṃ tathā adho; "
msgstr "as below, so above; as above, so below; "

msgctxt "sn51.20:2.7"
msgid "yathā divā tathā rattiṃ yathā rattiṃ tathā divā. "
msgstr "as by day, so by night; as by night, so by day. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:2.8"
msgid "Iti vivaṭena cetasā apariyonaddhena sappabhāsaṃ cittaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "And so, with an open and unenveloped heart, they develop a mind that’s full of radiance. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.20:2.9"
msgid "Vīriyasamādhi … pe … "
msgstr "They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to energy … "

msgctxt "sn51.20:2.10"
msgid "cittasamādhi … "
msgstr "mental development … "

msgctxt "sn51.20:2.11"
msgid "vīmaṃsāsamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti—"
msgstr "inquiry, and active effort. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:2.12"
msgid "iti me vīmaṃsā na ca atilīnā bhavissati, na ca atippaggahitā bhavissati, na ca ajjhattaṃ saṅkhittā bhavissati, na ca bahiddhā vikkhittā bhavissati. "
msgstr "They think: ‘My inquiry won’t be too lax or too tense. And it’ll be neither constricted internally nor scattered externally.’ "

msgctxt "sn51.20:2.13"
msgid "Pacchāpuresaññī ca viharati—"
msgstr "And they meditate perceiving continuity: "

msgctxt "sn51.20:2.14"
msgid "yathā pure tathā pacchā, yathā pacchā tathā pure; "
msgstr "as before, so after; as after, so before; "

msgctxt "sn51.20:2.15"
msgid "yathā adho tathā uddhaṃ, yathā uddhaṃ tathā adho; "
msgstr "as below, so above; as above, so below; "

msgctxt "sn51.20:2.16"
msgid "yathā divā tathā rattiṃ, yathā rattiṃ tathā divā. "
msgstr "as by day, so by night; as by night, so by day. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:2.17"
msgid "Iti vivaṭena cetasā apariyonaddhena sappabhāsaṃ cittaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "And so, with an open and unenveloped heart, they develop a mind that’s full of radiance. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn51.20:3.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, atilīno chando? "
msgstr "And what is enthusiasm that’s too lax? "

msgctxt "sn51.20:3.2"
msgid "Yo, bhikkhave, chando kosajjasahagato kosajjasampayutto—"
msgstr "It’s when enthusiasm is combined with laziness. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:3.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, atilīno chando. "
msgstr "This is called lax enthusiasm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn51.20:4.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, atippaggahito chando? "
msgstr "And what is enthusiasm that’s too tense? "

msgctxt "sn51.20:4.2"
msgid "Yo, bhikkhave, chando uddhaccasahagato uddhaccasampayutto—"
msgstr "It’s when enthusiasm is combined with restlessness. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:4.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, atippaggahito chando. "
msgstr "This is called tense enthusiasm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn51.20:5.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ saṅkhitto chando? "
msgstr "And what is enthusiasm that’s constricted internally? "

msgctxt "sn51.20:5.2"
msgid "Yo, bhikkhave, chando thinamiddhasahagato thinamiddhasampayutto—"
msgstr "It’s when enthusiasm is combined with dullness and drowsiness. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:5.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ saṅkhitto chando. "
msgstr "This is called enthusiasm constricted internally. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn51.20:6.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, bahiddhā vikkhitto chando? "
msgstr "And what is enthusiasm that’s distracted externally? "

msgctxt "sn51.20:6.2"
msgid "Yo, bhikkhave, chando bahiddhā pañca kāmaguṇe ārabbha anuvikkhitto anuvisaṭo—"
msgstr "It’s when enthusiasm is frequently distracted and diffused externally on account of the five kinds of sensual stimulation. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:6.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bahiddhā vikkhitto chando. "
msgstr "This is called enthusiasm distracted externally. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.278, sc7
msgctxt "sn51.20:7.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pacchāpuresaññī ca viharati—"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant meditate perceiving continuity: "

msgctxt "sn51.20:7.2"
msgid "yathā pure tathā pacchā, yathā pacchā tathā pure? "
msgstr "as before, so after; as after, so before? "

msgctxt "sn51.20:7.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno pacchāpuresaññā suggahitā hoti sumanasikatā sūpadhāritā suppaṭividdhā paññāya. "
msgstr "It’s when the perception of continuity is properly grasped, attended, borne in mind, and comprehended with wisdom by a mendicant. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:7.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pacchāpuresaññī ca viharati—"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant meditates perceiving continuity: "

msgctxt "sn51.20:7.5"
msgid "yathā pure tathā pacchā, yathā pacchā tathā pure. "
msgstr "as before, so after; as after, so before. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn51.20:8.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yathā adho tathā uddhaṃ, yathā uddhaṃ tathā adho viharati? "
msgstr "And how does a mendicant meditate as below, so above; as above, so below? "

msgctxt "sn51.20:8.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ uddhaṃ pādatalā adho kesamatthakā tacapariyantaṃ pūraṃ nānappakārassa asucino paccavekkhati: "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant examines their own body up from the soles of the feet and down from the tips of the hairs, wrapped in skin and full of many kinds of filth. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:8.3"
msgid "‘atthi imasmiṃ kāye kesā lomā nakhā dantā taco maṃsaṃ nhāru aṭṭhi aṭṭhimiñjaṃ vakkaṃ hadayaṃ yakanaṃ kilomakaṃ pihakaṃ papphāsaṃ antaṃ antaguṇaṃ udariyaṃ karīsaṃ pittaṃ semhaṃ pubbo lohitaṃ sedo medo assu vasā kheḷo siṅghāṇikā lasikā muttan’ti. "
msgstr "‘In this body there is head hair, body hair, nails, teeth, skin, flesh, sinews, bones, bone marrow, kidneys, heart, liver, diaphragm, spleen, lungs, intestines, mesentery, undigested food, feces, bile, phlegm, pus, blood, sweat, fat, tears, grease, saliva, snot, synovial fluid, urine.’ "

msgctxt "sn51.20:8.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yathā adho tathā uddhaṃ, yathā uddhaṃ tathā adho viharati. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant meditates as below, so above; as above, so below. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn51.20:9.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yathā divā tathā rattiṃ, yathā rattiṃ tathā divā viharati? "
msgstr "And how does a mendicant meditate as by day, so by night; as by night, so by day? "

msgctxt "sn51.20:9.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yehi ākārehi yehi liṅgehi yehi nimittehi divā chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti, so tehi ākārehi tehi liṅgehi tehi nimittehi rattiṃ chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm, and active effort, with the same features, attributes, and signs by day as by night. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:9.3"
msgid "yehi vā pana ākārehi yehi liṅgehi yehi nimittehi rattiṃ chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti, so tehi ākārehi tehi liṅgehi tehi nimittehi divā chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "And they develop it with the same features, attributes, and signs by night as by day. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:9.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yathā divā tathā rattiṃ, yathā rattiṃ tathā divā viharati. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant meditates as by day, so by night; as by night, so by day. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn51.20:10.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivaṭena cetasā apariyonaddhena sappabhāsaṃ cittaṃ bhāveti? "
msgstr "And how, with an open and unenveloped heart, does a mendicant develop a mind that’s full of radiance? "

msgctxt "sn51.20:10.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno ālokasaññā suggahitā hoti divāsaññā svādhiṭṭhitā. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant has properly grasped the perception of light, and has properly grasped the perception of day. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:10.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivaṭena cetasā apariyonaddhena sappabhāsaṃ cittaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "That’s how, with an open and unenveloped heart, a mendicant develops a mind that’s full of radiance. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.279, sc11
msgctxt "sn51.20:11.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, atilīnaṃ vīriyaṃ? "
msgstr "And what is energy that’s too lax? … "

msgctxt "sn51.20:11.2"
msgid "Yaṃ, bhikkhave, vīriyaṃ kosajjasahagataṃ kosajjasampayuttaṃ—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn51.20:11.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, atilīnaṃ vīriyaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn51.20:12.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, atippaggahitaṃ vīriyaṃ? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn51.20:12.2"
msgid "Yaṃ, bhikkhave, vīriyaṃ uddhaccasahagataṃ uddhaccasampayuttaṃ—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn51.20:12.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, atippaggahitaṃ vīriyaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn51.20:13.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ saṅkhittaṃ vīriyaṃ? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn51.20:13.2"
msgid "Yaṃ, bhikkhave, vīriyaṃ thinamiddhasahagataṃ thinamiddhasampayuttaṃ—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn51.20:13.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ saṅkhittaṃ vīriyaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn51.20:14.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, bahiddhā vikkhittaṃ vīriyaṃ? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn51.20:14.2"
msgid "Yaṃ, bhikkhave, vīriyaṃ bahiddhā pañca kāmaguṇe ārabbha anuvikkhittaṃ anuvisaṭaṃ—idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bahiddhā vikkhittaṃ vīriyaṃ … pe …. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "sn51.20:15.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivaṭena cetasā apariyonaddhena sappabhāsaṃ cittaṃ bhāveti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn51.20:15.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno ālokasaññā suggahitā hoti divāsaññā svādhiṭṭhitā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn51.20:15.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivaṭena cetasā apariyonaddhena sappabhāsaṃ cittaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "sn51.20:16.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, atilīnaṃ cittaṃ? "
msgstr "And what is mental development that’s too lax? … "

msgctxt "sn51.20:16.2"
msgid "Yaṃ, bhikkhave, cittaṃ kosajjasahagataṃ kosajjasampayuttaṃ—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn51.20:16.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, atilīnaṃ cittaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "sn51.20:17.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, atippaggahitaṃ cittaṃ? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn51.20:17.2"
msgid "Yaṃ, bhikkhave, cittaṃ uddhaccasahagataṃ uddhaccasampayuttaṃ—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn51.20:17.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, atippaggahitaṃ cittaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "sn51.20:18.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ saṅkhittaṃ cittaṃ? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn51.20:18.2"
msgid "Yaṃ, bhikkhave, cittaṃ thinamiddhasahagataṃ thinamiddhasampayuttaṃ—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn51.20:18.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ saṅkhittaṃ cittaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.280, sc19
msgctxt "sn51.20:19.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, bahiddhā vikkhittaṃ cittaṃ? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn51.20:19.2"
msgid "Yaṃ, bhikkhave, cittaṃ bahiddhā pañca kāmaguṇe ārabbha anuvikkhittaṃ anuvisaṭaṃ—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn51.20:19.3"
msgid "idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bahiddhā vikkhittaṃ cittaṃ … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn51.20:19.4"
msgid "evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivaṭena cetasā apariyonaddhena sappabhāsaṃ cittaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "sn51.20:20.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, atilīnā vīmaṃsā? "
msgstr "And what is inquiry that’s too lax? "

msgctxt "sn51.20:20.2"
msgid "Yā, bhikkhave, vīmaṃsā kosajjasahagatā kosajjasampayuttā—"
msgstr "It’s when inquiry is combined with laziness. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:20.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, atilīnā vīmaṃsā. "
msgstr "This is called lax inquiry. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "sn51.20:21.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, atippaggahitā vīmaṃsā? "
msgstr "And what is inquiry that’s too tense? "

msgctxt "sn51.20:21.2"
msgid "Yā, bhikkhave, vīmaṃsā uddhaccasahagatā uddhaccasampayuttā—"
msgstr "It’s when inquiry is combined with restlessness. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:21.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, atippaggahitā vīmaṃsā. "
msgstr "This is called tense inquiry. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "sn51.20:22.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ saṅkhittā vīmaṃsā? "
msgstr "And what is inquiry that’s constricted internally? "

msgctxt "sn51.20:22.2"
msgid "Yā, bhikkhave, vīmaṃsā thinamiddhasahagatā thinamiddhasampayuttā—"
msgstr "It’s when inquiry is combined with dullness and drowsiness. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:22.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ saṅkhittā vīmaṃsā. "
msgstr "This is called inquiry constricted internally. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "sn51.20:23.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, bahiddhā vikkhittā vīmaṃsā? "
msgstr "And what is inquiry that’s distracted externally? "

msgctxt "sn51.20:23.2"
msgid "Yā, bhikkhave, vīmaṃsā bahiddhā pañca kāmaguṇe ārabbha anuvikkhittā anuvisaṭā—"
msgstr "It’s when inquiry is frequently distracted and diffused externally on account of the five kinds of sensual stimulation. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:23.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bahiddhā vikkhittā vīmaṃsā … pe … "
msgstr "This is called inquiry distracted externally. … "

msgctxt "sn51.20:23.4"
msgid "evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivaṭena cetasā apariyonaddhena sappabhāsaṃ cittaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "That’s how, with an open and unenveloped heart, a mendicant develops a mind that’s full of radiance. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:23.5"
msgid "Evaṃ bhāvitā kho, bhikkhave, cattāro iddhipādā evaṃ bahulīkatā mahapphalā honti mahānisaṃsā. "
msgstr "When the four bases of psychic power have been developed and cultivated in this way they’re very fruitful and beneficial. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.281, sc24
msgctxt "sn51.20:24.1"
msgid "Evaṃ bhāvitesu kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu catūsu iddhipādesu evaṃ bahulīkatesu, anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhoti—ekopi hutvā bahudhā hoti, bahudhāpi hutvā eko hoti … pe … yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteti. "
msgstr "When the four bases of psychic power have been developed and cultivated in this way, a mendicant wields the many kinds of psychic power: multiplying themselves and becoming one again … controlling the body as far as the Brahmā realm. "

msgctxt "sn51.20:24.2"
msgid "Evaṃ bhāvitesu kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu catūsu iddhipādesu evaṃ bahulīkatesu, āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī”ti. "
msgstr "When the four bases of psychic power have been developed and cultivated in this way, they realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn51.20:24.3"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn51.20:24.4"
msgid "Pāsādakampanavaggo dutiyo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc25
msgctxt "sn51.20:25.1"
msgid "Pubbaṃ mahapphalaṃ chandaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn51.20:25.2"
msgid "Moggallānañca uṇṇābhaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn51.20:25.3"
msgid "Dve samaṇabrāhmaṇā bhikkhu, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn51.20:25.4"
msgid "Desanā vibhaṅgena cāti. "
msgstr ""

